urce/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 241, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Democratic_People's_Party_(Hungary)\", \"score\": 0.9945441123194101, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"KDNP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Democratic_People's_Party_(Hungary)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Democratic_People's_Party_(Hungary)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The vice president\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 190}, {\"ngram\": \"toFacebook\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 262}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremonial opening\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"a world event\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"an outright and brazen insult\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 383}, {\"ngram\": \"a major religion\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The greatness of sport, the ruling alliance junior party VP explained, lies precisely in its ability to unite people regardless of differences in taste and beliefs.\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 464, \"end\": 466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Pence\", \"score\": 0.9053715739743811, \"rank\": 0.08726836177789377, \"text\": \"VP\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Pence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Pence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The greatness\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 420}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 429}, {\"ngram\": \"its ability\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 523}, {\"ngram\": \"differences\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"taste\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"beliefs\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics is a peaceful competition, a celebration of endurance and sportsmanship, and this is what the opening ceremony has utterly spoiled.\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"a peaceful competition\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"endurance\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 639}, {\"ngram\": \"sportsmanship\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 657}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scene twisting the last supper into a distortion goes against everything that the Olympic ideal and human decency stand for.\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The scene\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"the last supper\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"a distortion\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic ideal\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"human decency\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not unifying, but divisive, it is not uplifting but outrageous,\\\" the Christian Democrat politician posted.\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_democracy\", \"score\": 0.9987715720375825, \"rank\": 0.0012299388536456048, \"text\": \"Christian Democrat\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_democracy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_democracy\"}, {\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_democracy\", \"score\": 0.9987715720375825, \"rank\": 0.0012299388536456048, \"text\": \"Christian Democrat\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_democracy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_democracy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bence Retvari pointed out that violating the beliefs of two billion people is unacceptable, and so is deliberately mocking the beliefs of others.\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 1106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bence Retvari\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"the beliefs\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"two billion people\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1035}, {\"ngram\": \"the beliefs\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, in a country whose culture has Christian roots, this is particularly enraging.\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1148, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9204404830279759, \"rank\": 0.08643635132964028, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"whose culture\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1143}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The KDNP vice-president posed the question, was there not a single sensible person who would have said that this is going too far, let us leave it out.\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1201, \"end\": 1205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Democratic_People's_Party_(Hungary)\", \"score\": 0.9945441123194101, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"KDNP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Democratic_People's_Party_(Hungary)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Democratic_People's_Party_(Hungary)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1220}, {\"ngram\": \"the question\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"not a single sensible person\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1334}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or were there many such people who thought so, but no one dared say so, because they were afraid of being immediately stigmatized by LGBT activists and would promptly lose their livelihoods?\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1482, \"end\": 1486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9982303712784207, \"rank\": 0.0013514457636890792, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many such people\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1379}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1406}, {\"ngram\": \"their livelihoods\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1538}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the latter is the case, this is also a shame, the politician stated, noting that \\\"perhaps the burned down Notre Dame should not be rebuilt in a country where Christianity is an object of mockery, but in a country where it is an object of pride\\\".\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999662402306811, \"rank\": 3.2960177175481226e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the latter\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"a shame\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"the politician\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"perhaps the burned down Notre Dame\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"an object\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"mockery\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"an object\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"pride\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added that \\\"many people have said that they dare to do such things to Christians because Christians are peaceful, but not to Muslims because the city would be in flames the next day.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1864, \"end\": 1874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.5558883129096303, \"rank\": 0.7989164562024853, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}, {\"begin\": 1883, \"end\": 1893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.5558883129096303, \"rank\": 0.7989164562024853, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}, {\"begin\": 1919, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.6110919249399765, \"rank\": 0.6364134470826273, \"text\": \"Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1817}, {\"ngram\": \"such things\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"flames\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 1962}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the fact that we are not aggressive does not mean that this can be done to us, and we do not have to tolerate it,\\\" he said, stating that this is intolerable.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He stressed the need to give voice to the protest in every way, and then urged like minded individuals to sign the petition at the following link:Citizengo.org:Defend our faith!\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2316, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\":